The national government has been urged to urgently drive out gun-brandishing Somali herders from Ukasi, Kitui town.Kitui Senator David Musila said police reservists should be hired from the local community living on the Tana River-Kitui border to end deadly conflict.&ldquo;We want the government to immediately drive the bandits out of our county or provide the locals with firearms to defend themselves,&rdquo; he said.He spoke on Friday at Ukasi market in Mwingi Central. The area has been hit by banditry attacks which have left 25 people dead and 2,000 others displaced in a year. Some residents are living in makeshift camps in Sosoma. Herders have encroached on Kitui land in search of pasture for their camels.